Yes, you can use logical operators in Swift to achieve similar functionality as in Python. In Swift, the logical operators `&&` (logical AND) and `||` (logical OR) are used. Here's how you can write the equivalent of your Python statement in Swift:

```swift
if (a > 0 && i == j) || f < 3 {
    // do something
}
```

In this Swift code:

- `&&` is used for the logical AND operation.
- `||` is used for the logical OR operation.

The parentheses around `(a > 0 && i == j)` are optional but can help clarify the precedence of operations, ensuring that the conditions are evaluated as intended.
